Ceepass Digital Limited, which recently began operations as a digital bank has positioned itself as the bank for the future, with its digital platform, ceepass.com making the most of the mobile phone technology to give its growing customers the benefit of simple, safe and convenient banking from their mobile phones. “You can do a whole lot of other things such as buying airtime and data at 4% discount or making all kinds of bill payments right on your phone,” CEO of Ceepass, Adama J Adama revealed.<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-855323 size-large" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass1-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="740" height="740" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass1-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass1-300x300.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass1-150x150.jpg 150w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass1-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass1-80x80.jpg 80w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass1.jpg 2000w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px"> “You can do the other regular banking stuff such as opening a bank account, requesting for a loan, transferring funds or getting a dollar card without stepping into a bank hall, all transactions conducted at your convenience and in the comfort of your home,” he added. Those seeking financial empowerment towards targeted goals will get a break in Ceepass’ revolutionary method of achieving financial goals through strategic savings and investments that are fail-safe. In contrast to the old method of borrowing from banks, the digital platform encourages individuals to commit to daily, weekly or monthly savings over a period of time, with such Target Saving earning 15% profit on money saved at the end of the tenure. Other forms of investments on the platform, namely Fixed Saving and Investment in Agribusiness also reward customers with 12.5% monthly interest.<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-855324 size-large" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass3-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="740" height="740" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass3-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass3-300x300.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass3-150x150.jpg 150w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass3-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass3-80x80.jpg 80w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Ceepass3.jpg 2000w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px"> “In this, we are working to help Nigerians improve their saving habits,” Adama said.
CEEPASS Digital Limited, incorporated by the Corporate Affairs Commission (CAC) is powered by CBN-licensed Solid Allianze Microfinance Bank. The platform’s through partnership integrated the services of companies such as Paystack, Providus Bank and Leadway Assurance to power aspects of its services. The Savings service is powered By Solid Allianze Microfinance Bank, while airtime and bills payment service is powered by VTPass. The Contract Farming investment is powered by Farm4Me Agriculture Ltd, while Viable X Agribusiness Limited runs the Export Financing Investment on the platform.<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-855322 size-large" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Adama-768x1024.jpg" alt="" width="740" height="987" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Adama-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Adama-225x300.jpg 225w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Adama.jpg 810w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px"> Since its beta testing in October, over 22, 000 subscribers have enrolled on Ceepass and are already using the platform’s plethora of services.
